EVNT_LONG_DESC: Occupant fell, jumped or was ejected from moving vehicle
Animal or insect in vehicle interfered with driver
"Sub-Ped": pedestrian injured subsequent to collision, etc.
Passenger or non-motorist being towed or pushed on conveyance
Getting on/off stopped/parked vehicle (occupants only; must have physical contact w/ vehicle)
Vehicle towed or had been towing another vehicle
Vehicle forced by impact into another vehicle, pedalcyclist or pedestrian
Vehicle set in motion by non-driver (child released brakes, etc.)
At or on railroad right-of-way (not Light Rail)
Vehicle struck railroad car on roadway
Jackknife; trailer or towed vehicle struck towing vehicle
Detached trailing object struck other vehicle, non-motorist, or object
Vehicle door opened into adjacent traffic lane
Lost load, load moved or shifted
Stock: cow, calf, bull, steer, sheep, etc.
Wild animal, game (includes birds; not deer or elk)
Culvert, open low or high manhole
Jiggle bar or traffic snake for channelization
Bridge railing or parapet (on bridge or approach)
Pole – traffic signal and ped signal only
Tree branch or other vegetation overhead, etc.
Wire or cable across or over the road
Temporary sign or barricade in road, etc.
Permanent sign or barricade in/off road
Other equipment in or off road (includes parked trailer, boat)
Wrecker, street sweeper, snow plow or sanding equipment
Rock, brick or other solid wall
Other bump (not speed bump), pothole or pavement irregularity
Other overhead object (highway sign, signal head, etc.); not bridge
Low or high shoulder at pavement edge
Struck by rock or other object set in motion by other vehicle (incl. lost loads)
Struck by rock or other moving or flying object (not set in motion by vehicle)
View obscured by fence, sign, phone booth, etc.
Vehicle immersed in body of water
Crash related to another separate crash
Two-way traffic on divided roadway all routed to one side
Cell phone  (on PAR or driver in use)
Teenage driver in violation of graduated license pgm
Cell phone use witnessed by other participant
Non-fixed object, other or unknown type
"Sub-Bike": pedalcyclist injured subsequent to collision, etc.
Street Car/Trolley (on rails or overhead wire system) struck vehicle
Vehicle struck Street Car/Trolley (on rails or overhead wire system)
At or on street car or trolley right-of-way
Vehicle struck railroad equipment (not train) on tracks
Distracted by navigation system or GPS device
Loose object in vehicle struck occupant
Sliding or swerving due to wet, icy, slippery or loose surface (not gravel)
Rock(s), boulder (not gravel; not rock slide)
Vertical grade / hill present at crash location
View obscured by vertical grade / hill
View obscured by vehicle window conditions
Injured occupant of railway train, light rail, street car or cable car
